==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|dissertatio|dissertātiō, dissertātiōnem|lang=la}}, from {{term|dissertare|lang=la}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/ˌdɪsə(ɹ)ˈteɪʃən/|lang=en}}
* {{a|GenAm}} {{IPA|/ˌdɪsɚˈteɪʃən/|lang=en}}
* {{rhymes|eɪʃən|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A [[formal]] [[exposition]] of a [[subject]], especially a [[research]] paper that students write in order to complete the requirements for a [[doctoral]] [[degree]]; a [[thesis]].
# A lengthy [[lecture]] on a subject; a [[treatise]]; a [[discourse]]; a [[sermon]].

